Program: Outlook
Title: The laws of love
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csz37d
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 16 Jun 2019
When Jim met John, it was instant love. Despite John battling terminal illness and the fact that same sex marriage wasn't legal in their state, the couple was determined to get married. What they didn't realise is that their union would change the course of US legal history. Originally broadcast on the 28th April 2018. Presenter: Saskia Edwards Producers: Alice Gioia and Katy Davis Image: Jim and John on their wedding day on an aeroplane Credit: Jim Obergefell Show less